WEBVTT

00:36.917 --> 00:39.834
Captain, we have arrived

00:36.917 --> 00:39.834
at Tanuga IV.

00:39.875 --> 00:43.083
The away team has completed

00:39.875 --> 00:43.083
its survey of Dr. Apgar's work

00:43.125 --> 00:45.583
and is ready to return

00:43.125 --> 00:45.583
to the ship.

00:45.625 --> 00:46.875
Good.

00:50.041 --> 00:52.625
Oh, please... and feel free

00:52.667 --> 00:56.959
to examine the work

00:52.667 --> 00:56.959
of the other students, too.

01:01.458 --> 01:02.500
Hmm...

01:02.542 --> 01:05.208
Ensign Williams'

01:02.542 --> 01:05.208
striking style

01:05.250 --> 01:06.875
is heavily influenced

01:06.917 --> 01:09.041
by geometric

01:06.917 --> 01:09.041
constructivism.

01:16.500 --> 01:18.792
Lieutenant Wright has

01:16.500 --> 01:18.792
effectively fused

01:18.834 --> 01:21.250
the incongruities

01:18.834 --> 01:21.250
of the surrealists

01:21.291 --> 01:23.709
with the irrationality

01:21.291 --> 01:23.709
of Dadaism.

01:35.625 --> 01:36.875
Interesting.

01:36.917 --> 01:37.834
Oh.

01:37.875 --> 01:39.750
Thank you.

01:39.792 --> 01:41.917
In what way?

01:41.959 --> 01:45.750
While suggesting

01:41.959 --> 01:45.750
the free treatment of form

01:45.792 --> 01:47.250
usually attributed to fauvism

01:47.291 --> 01:52.125
this quite inappropriately

01:47.291 --> 01:52.125
attempts to juxtapose

01:52.166 --> 01:55.375
the disparate

01:52.166 --> 01:55.375
cubistic styles of

01:52.166 --> 01:55.375
Picasso and Leger.

01:55.417 --> 01:59.500
In addition, the use of color

01:55.417 --> 01:59.500
suggests a haphazard melange

01:59.542 --> 02:01.041
of clashing styles.

02:01.083 --> 02:02.792
Furthermore,

02:01.083 --> 02:02.792
the unsettling

02:01.083 --> 02:02.792
overtones

02:02.834 --> 02:04.166
of proto-Vulcan

02:02.834 --> 02:04.166
influences...

02:04.208 --> 02:06.208
Thank you... Mr. Data.

02:06.250 --> 02:07.333
You are welcome, sir.

02:07.375 --> 02:09.750
If I can be of

02:07.375 --> 02:09.750
further assistance...

02:09.792 --> 02:11.583
<i>No...</i> thank you.

02:15.041 --> 02:18.500
(<i> door opens and closes</i> )

02:18.542 --> 02:22.125
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

02:18.542 --> 02:22.125
<i>Stardate 43610.4:</i>

02:22.166 --> 02:24.625
<i>After completing a delivery</i>

02:22.166 --> 02:24.625
<i>of dicosilium</i>

02:24.667 --> 02:26.792
<i>to the Tanuga IV</i>

02:24.667 --> 02:26.792
<i>research station</i>

02:26.834 --> 02:30.166
<i>our away team has received</i>

02:26.834 --> 02:30.166
<i>an update from Dr. Nel Apgar</i>

02:30.208 --> 02:32.583
<i>on his efforts</i>

02:30.208 --> 02:32.583
<i>to create Krieger waves,</i>

02:32.625 --> 02:35.625
<i>a potentially valuable</i>

02:32.625 --> 02:35.625
<i>new power source.</i>

02:35.667 --> 02:37.542
Welcome back,

02:35.667 --> 02:37.542
Mr. La Forge.

02:37.583 --> 02:38.917
Thank you, sir.

02:38.959 --> 02:40.792
Where's Commander Riker?

02:40.834 --> 02:42.667
He's still down

02:40.834 --> 02:42.667
on the station, sir.

02:42.709 --> 02:44.875
Dr. Apgar wanted

02:42.709 --> 02:44.875
to have a word with him.

02:44.917 --> 02:47.000
Any problems?

02:47.041 --> 02:51.250
Not with the scientific part

02:47.041 --> 02:51.250
of the mission, no, sir.

02:51.291 --> 02:53.000
Riker to<i> Enterprise.</i>

02:53.041 --> 02:54.875
I'm ready to leave now.

02:54.917 --> 02:56.000
I'm sure Commander Riker

02:54.917 --> 02:56.000
will be able

02:56.041 --> 02:57.083
to explain

02:56.041 --> 02:57.083
everything, Captain.

02:57.125 --> 02:58.875
O'BRIEN:

02:57.125 --> 02:58.875
Stand by, Commander.

02:58.917 --> 03:01.208
Engaging transport.

03:01.250 --> 03:02.667
(<i> beeping</i> )

03:02.709 --> 03:04.667
(<i> machinery powering down</i> )

03:04.709 --> 03:06.583
Transporter Room to Engineering.

03:06.625 --> 03:08.208
I have a power drain.

03:18.083 --> 03:19.625
Transporter Room.

03:19.667 --> 03:21.542
Is Commander Riker aboard?

03:21.583 --> 03:25.375
O'BRIEN:

03:21.583 --> 03:25.375
Not yet, Captain. I'm having

03:21.583 --> 03:25.375
trouble clearing the signal.

03:33.333 --> 03:36.000
Transporter Room to Bridge.

03:36.041 --> 03:39.208
He's aboard.

03:40.792 --> 03:42.917
Why do you sound

03:40.792 --> 03:42.917
so surprised, Mr. O'Brien?

03:42.959 --> 03:44.834
Well, for a moment,

03:42.959 --> 03:44.834
we weren't sure

03:44.875 --> 03:46.667
you left the space

03:44.875 --> 03:46.667
station in time.

03:46.709 --> 03:48.250
In time for what?

03:48.291 --> 03:51.583
It just exploded, sir.

04:23.959 --> 04:28.125
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

04:28.166 --> 04:32.375
<i>These are the voyages</i>

04:28.166 --> 04:32.375
<i>of the Starship</i> Enterprise.

04:32.417 --> 04:34.125
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

04:34.166 --> 04:38.166
<i>to explore</i>

04:34.166 --> 04:38.166
<i>strange new worlds...</i>

04:38.208 --> 04:42.750
<i>to seek out new life</i>

04:38.208 --> 04:42.750
<i>and new civilizations...</i>

04:42.792 --> 04:47.375
<i>to boldly go</i>

04:42.792 --> 04:47.375
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

05:46.750 --> 05:48.667
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental:</i>

05:48.709 --> 05:50.417
<i>Commander Riker has informed me</i>

05:50.458 --> 05:53.333
<i>that Dr. Apgar was the only one</i>

05:50.458 --> 05:53.333
<i>aboard the space station</i>

05:53.375 --> 05:55.166
<i>when it exploded.</i>

05:55.208 --> 05:59.542
<i>We remain in orbit</i>

05:55.208 --> 05:59.542
<i>investigating the accident.</i>

05:59.583 --> 06:01.792
I've gone through

05:59.583 --> 06:01.792
the whole system, Captain.

06:01.834 --> 06:05.166
I can't find any malfunction

06:01.834 --> 06:05.166
in the transporter

06:05.208 --> 06:07.667
or nothing that would cause

06:05.208 --> 06:07.667
an explosion like that.

06:07.709 --> 06:09.875
Why was there

06:07.709 --> 06:09.875
a power drain

06:07.709 --> 06:09.875
before transport?

06:09.917 --> 06:11.041
I don't know, sir.

06:11.083 --> 06:12.834
I shall want an

06:11.083 --> 06:12.834
answer to that.

06:12.875 --> 06:14.542
I'm sure the

06:12.875 --> 06:14.542
Tanugans will, too.

06:14.583 --> 06:15.834
Yes, sir.

06:15.875 --> 06:17.583
Captain, the radiation

06:15.875 --> 06:17.583
and debris

06:17.625 --> 06:20.709
are consistent with an overload

06:17.625 --> 06:20.709
of the station's reactor core.

06:20.750 --> 06:22.834
Were there

06:20.750 --> 06:22.834
any indications

06:22.875 --> 06:24.250
of reactor

06:22.875 --> 06:24.250
core problems

06:24.291 --> 06:25.500
while you were

06:24.291 --> 06:25.500
on the station?

06:25.542 --> 06:26.458
No, sir.

06:26.500 --> 06:28.375
Number One?

06:30.417 --> 06:32.917
Mr. La Forge indicated

06:32.959 --> 06:35.583
that this was not

06:32.959 --> 06:35.583
an entirely routine mission.

06:35.625 --> 06:36.959
It's a long story, sir

06:37.041 --> 06:39.750
but I'm sure it doesn't have

06:37.041 --> 06:39.750
anything to do

06:39.792 --> 06:40.709
with this accident.

06:40.750 --> 06:42.500
(<i> communications beep</i> )

06:42.542 --> 06:45.583
Captain, Chief Investigator Krag

06:42.542 --> 06:45.583
of the Tanugan security force

06:45.625 --> 06:47.458
requests permission

06:45.625 --> 06:47.458
to beam aboard.

06:47.500 --> 06:50.125
Granted. Will you

06:47.500 --> 06:50.125
escort him to the

06:47.500 --> 06:50.125
Bridge, Mr. Worf?

06:50.166 --> 06:53.375
WORF:

06:50.166 --> 06:53.375
Aye, sir.

06:53.417 --> 06:57.125
Perhaps you had better tell me

06:53.417 --> 06:57.125
as much as possible

06:57.166 --> 07:00.166
prior to his arrival,

06:57.166 --> 07:00.166
Number One.

07:01.875 --> 07:03.375
(<i> sighing</i> )

07:12.750 --> 07:15.583
I'm Lieutenant Worf,

07:12.750 --> 07:15.583
head of ship's security.

07:15.625 --> 07:17.417
I will take you to the Captain.

07:24.875 --> 07:26.500
Chief Investigator,

07:26.542 --> 07:28.834
welcome to

07:26.542 --> 07:28.834
the<i> Enterprise.</i>

07:28.875 --> 07:30.458
I'm Captain Picard.

07:30.500 --> 07:32.458
This is my

07:30.500 --> 07:32.458
First Officer

07:32.500 --> 07:34.375
Commander

07:32.500 --> 07:34.375
William Riker.

07:34.417 --> 07:38.917
Commander Riker, I am here

07:34.417 --> 07:38.917
to take you into custody.

07:38.959 --> 07:41.041
Custody? On what charge?

07:41.083 --> 07:42.875
Suspicion of murder.

07:42.917 --> 07:45.000
Murder? Now, wait a minute.

07:42.917 --> 07:45.000
You can't come on...

07:45.041 --> 07:46.458
Chief Investigator...

07:46.500 --> 07:48.667
we are perfectly willing

07:46.500 --> 07:48.667
to cooperate with you...

07:48.709 --> 07:49.917
Then release the prisoner

07:49.959 --> 07:52.000
for transportation

07:49.959 --> 07:52.000
to the planet.

07:55.333 --> 07:58.125
Let's continue this

07:55.333 --> 07:58.125
discussion in private.

08:00.125 --> 08:04.125
Number One, you

08:00.125 --> 08:04.125
have the Bridge.

08:25.083 --> 08:28.333
Just what is the evidence

08:25.083 --> 08:28.333
against my officer?

08:28.375 --> 08:29.917
Two witnesses have come forward

08:29.959 --> 08:33.375
to describe Commander Riker's

08:29.959 --> 08:33.375
threats against Dr. Apgar.

08:33.417 --> 08:34.500
Threats?

08:34.542 --> 08:35.667
I'm aware there was

08:35.709 --> 08:37.500
a private conversation

08:35.709 --> 08:37.500
between them.

08:37.542 --> 08:40.250
Apparently, it was much more

08:37.542 --> 08:40.250
than just a private conversation

08:40.291 --> 08:43.792
but he will be given a chance

08:40.291 --> 08:43.792
to prove his innocence.

08:43.834 --> 08:47.291
Investigator, in our system

08:43.834 --> 08:47.291
of jurisprudence,

08:47.333 --> 08:50.375
a man is innocent

08:47.333 --> 08:50.375
until proved guilty.

08:50.417 --> 08:53.709
In ours, he is guilty

08:50.417 --> 08:53.709
until he is proved innocent,

08:53.750 --> 08:56.166
and you are under

08:53.750 --> 08:56.166
our jurisdiction.

08:56.208 --> 08:59.583
If I understand Federation

08:56.208 --> 08:59.583
regulations on this matter,

08:59.625 --> 09:02.125
and I just happened

08:59.625 --> 09:02.125
to look them up...

09:02.166 --> 09:04.750
I am aware of Federation

09:02.166 --> 09:04.750
regulations, sir,

09:04.792 --> 09:07.083
and if you investigate

09:04.792 --> 09:07.083
them further

09:07.125 --> 09:09.208
you will find

09:07.125 --> 09:09.208
the Captain decides

09:09.250 --> 09:11.083
if extradition

09:09.250 --> 09:11.083
is warranted.

09:11.125 --> 09:12.709
Are you saying it is not?

09:12.750 --> 09:16.000
I am saying

09:12.750 --> 09:16.000
if there is sufficient cause

09:16.041 --> 09:17.417
to warrant a trial,

09:17.458 --> 09:21.000
I will release my officer

09:17.458 --> 09:21.000
into your custody.

09:21.041 --> 09:24.834
Would you say that you are close

09:21.041 --> 09:24.834
to your First Officer, Captain?

09:24.875 --> 09:27.542
That question

09:24.875 --> 09:27.542
is irrelevant here.

09:27.583 --> 09:29.834
Really, Captain,

09:27.583 --> 09:29.834
you cannot believe that.

09:29.875 --> 09:32.875
How can I expect

09:29.875 --> 09:32.875
a fair and impartial decision?

09:32.917 --> 09:35.834
I must protect the

09:32.917 --> 09:35.834
rights of my officer.

09:35.875 --> 09:37.208
I can appreciate that,

09:37.250 --> 09:41.834
but you will do it

09:37.250 --> 09:41.834
on the planet, not here.

09:41.875 --> 09:45.500
After all, what if you

09:41.875 --> 09:45.500
were suddenly to decide

09:45.542 --> 09:47.500
to leave this star system?

09:47.542 --> 09:50.875
You have my word

09:47.542 --> 09:50.875
as a Starfleet officer

09:50.917 --> 09:52.291
that I will not.

09:54.166 --> 09:55.834
Unacceptable.

09:55.875 --> 10:00.000
Captain, you will turn him over

09:55.875 --> 10:00.000
to me for interrogation now.

10:02.792 --> 10:04.166
Interrogate him here.

10:04.208 --> 10:08.834
We must re-create step by step,

10:04.208 --> 10:08.834
moment by moment,

10:08.875 --> 10:10.417
all the events

10:10.458 --> 10:12.125
leading to the explosion.

10:12.166 --> 10:14.583
We will require access

10:12.166 --> 10:14.583
to all the witnesses

10:14.625 --> 10:18.375
as well as the data

10:14.625 --> 10:18.375
from the lab's ground computers.

10:18.417 --> 10:21.750
It would be impossible

10:18.417 --> 10:21.750
to accomplish here.

10:21.792 --> 10:23.375
Perhaps not.

10:23.417 --> 10:24.709
Mr. Data, will you report

10:24.750 --> 10:25.875
to my ready room?

10:25.917 --> 10:26.959
DATA: Aye, sir.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.000
We may be able to assist you

10:29.041 --> 10:31.291
in re-creating these events.

10:33.291 --> 10:37.166
Commander Data, this is

10:33.291 --> 10:37.166
Chief Inspector Krag.

10:37.208 --> 10:39.458
Commander, by

10:37.208 --> 10:39.458
taking testimony

10:39.500 --> 10:40.959
from the away team

10:41.000 --> 10:43.875
and from witnesses provided

10:41.000 --> 10:43.875
by the Investigator,

10:43.917 --> 10:46.417
would it be possible

10:43.917 --> 10:46.417
to program the holodeck

10:46.458 --> 10:49.792
to re-create what happened

10:46.458 --> 10:49.792
on the science station?

10:49.834 --> 10:52.875
It would require construction

10:49.834 --> 10:52.875
and design specifications

10:52.917 --> 10:55.041
full orthographic

10:52.917 --> 10:55.041
representations

10:55.083 --> 10:56.792
of the Krieger equipment

10:56.834 --> 10:58.625
as well as visual

10:56.834 --> 10:58.625
representations

10:58.667 --> 11:01.083
and voice analyses

10:58.667 --> 11:01.083
of the persons involved,

11:01.125 --> 11:04.250
but it is possible.

11:05.458 --> 11:07.458
Very well.

11:07.500 --> 11:10.291
Arrangements will be

11:07.500 --> 11:10.291
made to provide you

11:10.333 --> 11:12.458
with all available

11:10.333 --> 11:12.458
information.

11:12.500 --> 11:15.458
I shall return shortly

11:12.500 --> 11:15.458
with our witnesses.

11:15.500 --> 11:18.917
Commander, will you escort

11:15.500 --> 11:18.917
Investigator Krag

11:18.959 --> 11:20.834
to Transporter Room Three?

11:35.166 --> 11:37.208
Ensign Crusher,

11:35.166 --> 11:37.208
Mr. La Forge...

11:37.250 --> 11:40.125
we are going

11:37.250 --> 11:40.125
to re-create the

11:37.250 --> 11:40.125
research station

11:40.166 --> 11:41.750
here on the holodeck.

11:41.792 --> 11:44.250
I want you to work

11:41.792 --> 11:44.250
with Commander Data

11:41.792 --> 11:44.250
on the preparations.

11:44.291 --> 11:48.125
In addition,

11:44.291 --> 11:48.125
Commander La Forge

11:44.291 --> 11:48.125
and Commander Riker,

11:48.166 --> 11:49.542
I want you to

11:48.166 --> 11:49.542
give the computer

11:49.583 --> 11:52.208
detailed depositions

11:49.583 --> 11:52.208
of everything you saw,

11:52.250 --> 11:54.625
everything you heard

11:52.250 --> 11:54.625
while you were on board.

11:54.667 --> 12:00.125
Counselor, I want

11:54.667 --> 12:00.125
you to assist me

11:54.667 --> 12:00.125
during this inquiry.

12:03.792 --> 12:07.250
My decision about

12:03.792 --> 12:07.250
the extradition will be based

12:07.291 --> 12:12.041
on the evidence presented

12:07.291 --> 12:12.041
during these re-creations.

12:14.291 --> 12:15.709
Captain...

12:17.792 --> 12:19.792
May I have a word with you?

12:19.834 --> 12:22.166
Under the circumstances,

12:19.834 --> 12:22.166
Number One,

12:22.208 --> 12:24.208
I think that would be

12:22.208 --> 12:24.208
inappropriate.

12:36.500 --> 12:41.583
DATA:

12:36.500 --> 12:41.583
<i>Second Officer's Log,</i>

12:36.500 --> 12:41.583
<i>Stardate 43611.6:</i>

12:41.625 --> 12:45.333
<i>Programming of the holodeck</i>

12:41.625 --> 12:45.333
<i>has taken 18 hours, 11 minutes</i>

12:45.375 --> 12:47.166
<i>and is now complete.</i>

12:47.208 --> 12:50.000
<i>All participants have entered</i>

12:47.208 --> 12:50.000
<i>their depositions.</i>

12:50.041 --> 12:52.542
<i>Technical schematics</i>

12:50.041 --> 12:52.542
<i>and complete records</i>

12:52.583 --> 12:54.375
<i>from the lab's</i>

12:52.583 --> 12:54.375
<i>ground computers</i>

12:54.417 --> 12:56.208
<i>as well as Dr. Apgar's</i>

12:54.417 --> 12:56.208
<i>personal logs</i>

12:56.250 --> 12:57.250
<i>have been included.</i>

12:57.291 --> 12:58.500
<i>The re-creations will have</i>

12:58.542 --> 13:02.041
<i>a nominal 8.7%</i>

12:58.542 --> 13:02.041
<i>margin of error.</i>

13:09.625 --> 13:11.625
(<i> door begins closing</i> )

13:27.875 --> 13:29.792
Is there anything

13:27.875 --> 13:29.792
you'd like to say

13:29.834 --> 13:31.500
before we begin,

13:29.834 --> 13:31.500
Number One?

13:31.542 --> 13:33.083
Just this.

13:33.125 --> 13:35.166
I'm not a murderer.

13:35.208 --> 13:36.625
I went to the

13:35.208 --> 13:36.625
Tanugan lab

13:36.667 --> 13:39.083
as an official

13:36.667 --> 13:39.083
representative

13:36.667 --> 13:39.083
of Starfleet.

13:39.125 --> 13:40.792
I acted accordingly.

13:40.834 --> 13:44.000
I was there to evaluate

13:40.834 --> 13:44.000
Dr. Apgar's progress

13:44.041 --> 13:45.333
in the development

13:45.375 --> 13:47.291
of a Krieger-wave

13:45.375 --> 13:47.291
converter.

13:47.333 --> 13:50.208
That's all I was

13:47.333 --> 13:50.208
interested in.

13:50.250 --> 13:51.417
Computer...

13:51.458 --> 13:52.834
(<i> beeping</i> )

13:52.875 --> 13:54.458
...load deposition program

13:54.500 --> 13:56.083
Riker One.

13:57.834 --> 13:59.500
Run the simulation.

14:05.333 --> 14:07.250
Dr. Apgar?

14:07.291 --> 14:08.792
I'm Commander

14:07.291 --> 14:08.792
William Riker.

14:08.834 --> 14:10.917
Lieutenant Commander

14:08.834 --> 14:10.917
Geordi La Forge.

14:10.959 --> 14:12.625
My assistant, Tayna.

14:12.667 --> 14:15.667
Well, let's get on

14:12.667 --> 14:15.667
with it, shall we?

14:15.709 --> 14:17.917
Let's not be in

14:15.709 --> 14:17.917
such a hurry, dear.

14:17.959 --> 14:19.000
Perhaps our guest

14:19.041 --> 14:21.500
would care for

14:19.041 --> 14:21.500
some refreshments?

14:21.542 --> 14:23.375
My wife, Manua.

14:23.417 --> 14:25.166
RIKER:

14:23.417 --> 14:25.166
A pleasure to meet you,

14:23.417 --> 14:25.166
Mrs. Apgar.

14:25.208 --> 14:27.917
If you're prepared to start,

14:25.208 --> 14:27.917
so are we.

14:27.959 --> 14:30.083
Of course,

14:27.959 --> 14:30.083
I'm prepared.

14:30.125 --> 14:31.750
All right. Why

14:30.125 --> 14:31.750
don't you give me

14:31.792 --> 14:33.500
an overview of

14:31.792 --> 14:33.500
your research

14:33.542 --> 14:35.208
while Mr. La Forge

14:33.542 --> 14:35.208
and your assistant

14:35.250 --> 14:36.333
take a look at the

14:35.250 --> 14:36.333
experimental data.

14:36.375 --> 14:38.625
Fine, whatever.

14:38.667 --> 14:40.959
I must say, Commander, I

14:38.667 --> 14:40.959
resent this early arrival.

14:41.000 --> 14:42.500
Starfleet will get

14:41.000 --> 14:42.500
its converter.

14:42.542 --> 14:44.583
I've had a few

14:42.542 --> 14:44.583
setbacks, that's all.

14:44.625 --> 14:47.041
We're not here to

14:44.625 --> 14:47.041
pressure you, Doctor.

14:47.083 --> 14:48.875
We just want an update

14:47.083 --> 14:48.875
on your progress.

14:48.917 --> 14:51.166
Tayna, show the

14:48.917 --> 14:51.166
Commander's assistant

14:51.208 --> 14:53.750
whatever he wants to

14:51.208 --> 14:53.750
see. Give him full

14:51.208 --> 14:53.750
access to our records.

14:53.792 --> 14:55.000
TAYNA:

14:53.792 --> 14:55.000
Yes, Doctor.

14:55.041 --> 14:56.458
If you'll

14:55.041 --> 14:56.458
come with me.

14:56.500 --> 14:58.333
Our lambda

14:56.500 --> 14:58.333
field generator

14:58.375 --> 15:00.000
is on the planet

14:58.375 --> 15:00.000
since it requires

15:00.041 --> 15:01.709
a minimum

15:00.041 --> 15:01.709
of 5,000 kilometers

15:01.750 --> 15:03.250
for the field

15:01.750 --> 15:03.250
to collimate.

15:03.291 --> 15:04.959
Really, darling,

15:03.291 --> 15:04.959
you're being rude.

15:05.000 --> 15:06.625
After all,

15:05.000 --> 15:06.625
Commander Riker is willing

15:06.667 --> 15:08.625
to sit through all your prattle

15:06.667 --> 15:08.625
about Krieger waves.

15:08.667 --> 15:10.500
Let's have a drink, Commander,

15:10.542 --> 15:13.083
and we'll hear

15:10.542 --> 15:13.083
all about Krieger waves.

15:23.709 --> 15:25.417
To your success, Doctor.

15:25.458 --> 15:26.875
Mm-hmm.

15:26.917 --> 15:29.542
And the rewards

15:26.917 --> 15:29.542
that come with it.

15:31.125 --> 15:33.041
Riker, what is Starfleet

15:31.125 --> 15:33.041
doing here anyway?

15:33.083 --> 15:35.750
My delivery wasn't scheduled

15:33.083 --> 15:35.750
for another three months.

15:35.792 --> 15:38.125
Well, we were in this sector

15:35.792 --> 15:38.125
on another mission,

15:38.166 --> 15:40.500
and since you had already

15:38.166 --> 15:40.500
contacted Starfleet

15:40.542 --> 15:41.959
about additional dicosilium,

15:42.000 --> 15:43.834
it seemed like

15:42.000 --> 15:43.834
a good opportunity.

15:43.875 --> 15:45.208
How interesting.

15:45.250 --> 15:47.583
Tell us about

15:45.250 --> 15:47.583
this other mission.

15:47.625 --> 15:49.375
It was just a study

15:47.625 --> 15:49.375
of a proto-star cloud.

15:49.417 --> 15:51.583
The<i> Enterprise</i>

15:49.417 --> 15:51.583
will be back tomorrow.

15:51.625 --> 15:54.000
The<i> Enterprise</i>

15:51.625 --> 15:54.000
just left you here?

15:54.041 --> 15:55.667
We didn't want

15:54.041 --> 15:55.667
to inconvenience you.

15:55.709 --> 15:57.625
We've made arrangements

15:55.709 --> 15:57.625
for quarters on the planet.

15:57.667 --> 15:59.875
Oh, I won't hear

15:57.667 --> 15:59.875
of such a thing.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.792
Commander, I insist you

15:59.917 --> 16:02.792
and Mr. La Forge stay with us.

16:02.834 --> 16:04.208
I hardly think...

16:04.250 --> 16:06.250
I know that you would prefer

16:04.250 --> 16:06.250
to be left alone

16:06.291 --> 16:08.709
with your very

16:06.291 --> 16:08.709
important work

16:08.750 --> 16:11.458
but I, for one,

16:08.750 --> 16:11.458
am glad for the company.

16:14.875 --> 16:16.959
Good.

16:17.000 --> 16:18.458
I must apologize

16:18.500 --> 16:20.542
for my husband's lack

16:18.500 --> 16:20.542
of social graces.

16:20.583 --> 16:22.250
He may be one

16:22.291 --> 16:24.750
of the great scientific minds

16:22.291 --> 16:24.750
in the galaxy, but...

16:24.792 --> 16:27.542
he does come up a bit short

16:24.792 --> 16:27.542
in other areas.

16:31.542 --> 16:32.625
KRAG:

16:31.542 --> 16:32.625
Wait a moment.

16:32.667 --> 16:34.875
Stop.

16:34.917 --> 16:36.667
Computer,

16:34.917 --> 16:36.667
freeze program.

16:36.709 --> 16:38.917
KRAG:

16:36.709 --> 16:38.917
Then it's your testimony

16:38.959 --> 16:40.500
that it was

16:38.959 --> 16:40.500
Mrs. Apgar's idea

16:40.542 --> 16:43.083
for you to spend the night

16:40.542 --> 16:43.083
aboard the space station?

16:43.125 --> 16:45.959
It's my testimony

16:43.125 --> 16:45.959
and it's the truth.

16:49.291 --> 16:50.959
Resume program.

16:54.792 --> 16:57.000
Our guest quarters

16:54.792 --> 16:57.000
aren't luxurious,

16:57.041 --> 16:59.709
but I've tried

16:57.041 --> 16:59.709
to make this room

16:57.041 --> 16:59.709
warm and inviting.

16:59.750 --> 17:01.500
I'll be very

16:59.750 --> 17:01.500
comfortable, thank you.

17:01.542 --> 17:03.792
Good night.

17:03.834 --> 17:06.375
The environmental

17:03.834 --> 17:06.375
controls are over here.

17:06.417 --> 17:08.083
I'm sure I'll find

17:06.417 --> 17:08.083
everything I need.

17:08.125 --> 17:11.959
And the door shuts

17:08.125 --> 17:11.959
by touching this panel.

17:14.834 --> 17:16.625
Mrs. Apgar...

17:16.667 --> 17:17.667
This is my sanctuary.

17:17.709 --> 17:19.417
Privacy is very important

17:19.458 --> 17:22.166
on a small station.

17:22.208 --> 17:27.291
I'm left alone here,

17:22.208 --> 17:27.291
often for hours.

17:27.333 --> 17:28.834
It's late.

17:28.875 --> 17:30.458
I am tired.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.291
Are you still tired,

17:32.000 --> 17:34.291
Commander?

17:34.333 --> 17:36.542
RIKER:

17:34.333 --> 17:36.542
Ma'am, excuse me.

17:36.583 --> 17:37.917
I really think

17:36.583 --> 17:37.917
that you ought to leave.

17:40.083 --> 17:41.792
I knew I'd find you

17:40.083 --> 17:41.792
with him.

17:41.834 --> 17:45.166
Did you think I didn't notice

17:41.834 --> 17:45.166
how you looked at him?

17:45.208 --> 17:47.375
I'm not the fool

17:45.208 --> 17:47.375
you take me for.

17:47.417 --> 17:48.625
RIKER:

17:47.417 --> 17:48.625
Doctor!

17:48.667 --> 17:50.959
(<i> groaning</i> )

17:51.000 --> 17:52.291
Doctor, believe me.

17:52.333 --> 17:54.291
This has been

17:52.333 --> 17:54.291
a terrible mistake.

17:54.333 --> 17:56.333
You won't get away with this.

17:56.375 --> 17:57.333
I'll see to it.

17:57.375 --> 17:59.208
I swear I

17:57.375 --> 17:59.208
will, Riker.

18:04.750 --> 18:05.917
Freeze program.

18:05.959 --> 18:07.542
I didn't

18:05.959 --> 18:07.542
see Dr. Apgar

18:07.583 --> 18:09.375
until the

18:07.583 --> 18:09.375
following morning

18:09.417 --> 18:11.333
when he asked

18:09.417 --> 18:11.333
to see me alone.

18:11.375 --> 18:14.542
Commander La Forge

18:11.375 --> 18:14.542
returned to the

18:11.375 --> 18:14.542
<i>Enterprise.</i>

18:14.583 --> 18:16.125
Resume program.

18:17.667 --> 18:20.625
I suppose if I make

18:17.667 --> 18:20.625
a formal complaint,

18:20.667 --> 18:22.750
your report on my work

18:20.667 --> 18:22.750
won't be very good.

18:22.792 --> 18:24.667
Doctor, this is going to have

18:22.792 --> 18:24.667
no impact on my report.

18:24.709 --> 18:26.959
It was a misunderstanding

18:24.709 --> 18:26.959
of the worst kind.

18:27.000 --> 18:29.333
We could straighten

18:27.000 --> 18:29.333
the entire thing out

18:29.375 --> 18:31.709
if you would ask

18:29.375 --> 18:31.709
Mrs. Apgar to join us.

18:31.750 --> 18:33.041
My wife and

18:31.750 --> 18:33.041
my assistant

18:33.083 --> 18:36.291
have transported

18:33.083 --> 18:36.291
down to the planet.

18:36.333 --> 18:37.750
What are you going

18:36.333 --> 18:37.750
to put in your

18:36.333 --> 18:37.750
report, Riker?

18:37.792 --> 18:40.166
That there is

18:37.792 --> 18:40.166
no justification

18:40.208 --> 18:41.667
for all the

18:40.208 --> 18:41.667
extra dicosilium

18:40.208 --> 18:41.667
I've requested?

18:41.709 --> 18:44.792
That is why they sent

18:41.709 --> 18:44.792
you early, isn't it?

18:44.834 --> 18:46.583
Doctor, I...

18:46.625 --> 18:47.917
NEL:

18:46.625 --> 18:47.917
I can explain

18:46.625 --> 18:47.917
why I needed it.

18:47.959 --> 18:49.625
They have no idea

18:47.959 --> 18:49.625
what my problems are.

18:49.667 --> 18:51.083
There are

18:49.667 --> 18:51.083
explanations for...

18:51.125 --> 18:53.208
I don't need

18:51.125 --> 18:53.208
explanations.

18:53.250 --> 18:57.625
Then we have nothing further

18:53.250 --> 18:57.625
to say to each other.

18:59.542 --> 19:02.250
I'll tell my Captain

18:59.542 --> 19:02.250
to expect your grievance.

19:02.291 --> 19:04.208
Do that.

19:07.083 --> 19:09.041
Riker to<i> Enterprise.</i>

19:09.083 --> 19:11.250
I'm ready to leave now.

19:11.291 --> 19:14.583
O'BRIEN:

19:11.291 --> 19:14.583
Stand by, Commander.

19:14.625 --> 19:17.041
Engaging transport.

19:17.083 --> 19:19.041
Freeze program.

19:19.083 --> 19:21.417
Then I returned

19:19.083 --> 19:21.417
to the<i> Enterprise.</i>

19:21.458 --> 19:24.208
And you have nothing further

19:21.458 --> 19:24.208
to add, Commander?

19:24.250 --> 19:26.417
Nothing about firing a phaser?

19:26.458 --> 19:30.000
I never fired a phaser

19:26.458 --> 19:30.000
on the science station.

19:30.041 --> 19:33.000
Well, that's odd... very odd.

19:33.041 --> 19:36.208
Captain Picard, is it not true

19:36.250 --> 19:37.834
that your sensors

19:36.250 --> 19:37.834
detected an energy drain

19:37.875 --> 19:41.291
just as Commander Riker

19:37.875 --> 19:41.291
began transport?

19:41.333 --> 19:42.625
That's correct.

19:42.667 --> 19:44.583
KRAG:

19:42.667 --> 19:44.583
Have you been able

19:42.667 --> 19:44.583
to explain it?

19:44.625 --> 19:46.083
PICARD:

19:44.625 --> 19:46.083
Not to my knowledge.

19:46.125 --> 19:47.750
We have.

19:51.625 --> 19:54.542
Our readings are

19:51.625 --> 19:54.542
quite clear about it.

19:54.583 --> 19:57.166
Information retrieved

19:54.583 --> 19:57.166
from the lab's ground computers

19:57.208 --> 20:00.625
indicate that a focused

19:57.208 --> 20:00.625
energy pulse was fired

20:00.667 --> 20:03.750
just as Commander Riker

20:00.667 --> 20:03.750
began transport.

20:03.792 --> 20:06.834
Furthermore, by analyzing

20:03.792 --> 20:06.834
the angle and trajectory,

20:06.875 --> 20:09.792
we have determined that

20:06.875 --> 20:09.792
it came from the very spot

20:09.834 --> 20:12.166
Commander Riker was standing.

20:17.208 --> 20:22.125
So then, will you allow me

20:17.208 --> 20:22.125
to show you my re-creation

20:22.166 --> 20:25.125
of the end of this story?

20:25.166 --> 20:27.834
A speculation,

20:25.166 --> 20:27.834
if you will.

20:27.875 --> 20:30.125
Computer...

20:30.166 --> 20:32.959
run hypothetical Krag one.

20:37.000 --> 20:38.875
Riker to<i> Enterprise.</i>

20:38.917 --> 20:40.625
I'm ready to leave now.

20:40.667 --> 20:42.333
O'BRIEN:

20:40.667 --> 20:42.333
Stand by, Commander.

20:42.375 --> 20:44.750
Engaging transport.

20:45.750 --> 20:47.875
KRAG:

20:45.750 --> 20:47.875
Freeze program.

20:47.917 --> 20:53.000
Three seconds later,

20:47.917 --> 20:53.000
the space station exploded.

21:07.834 --> 21:09.291
LA FORGE:

21:07.834 --> 21:09.291
The Tanugans are right.

21:09.333 --> 21:11.125
Something<i> was</i> fired

21:09.333 --> 21:11.125
at the reactor core

21:11.166 --> 21:12.250
just before transport.

21:12.291 --> 21:13.667
The energy signature

21:13.709 --> 21:15.834
would seem to indicate

21:13.709 --> 21:15.834
a phaser-like blast.

21:15.875 --> 21:17.667
Well, it<i> wasn't</i>

21:15.875 --> 21:17.667
the Commander's phaser.

21:17.709 --> 21:18.709
It couldn't have been.

21:18.750 --> 21:20.125
There's another answer.

21:20.166 --> 21:22.166
We're just not seeing it.

21:22.208 --> 21:23.667
Was there anything

21:22.208 --> 21:23.667
else in the lab

21:23.709 --> 21:26.291
capable of creating this

21:23.709 --> 21:26.291
kind of energy discharge?

21:26.333 --> 21:27.583
Not that I saw.

21:27.625 --> 21:29.208
Besides, how do you

21:27.625 --> 21:29.208
account for the fact

21:29.250 --> 21:31.625
that it came from

21:29.250 --> 21:31.625
Commander Riker's

21:29.250 --> 21:31.625
exact position?

21:31.667 --> 21:33.000
Damn it, I should've

21:31.667 --> 21:33.000
stayed with him.

21:33.041 --> 21:34.083
(<i> beeping</i> )

21:34.125 --> 21:35.625
Commander.

21:35.667 --> 21:37.500
Sensors indicate

21:35.667 --> 21:37.500
a radiation burst

21:37.542 --> 21:39.709
on deck 39

21:37.542 --> 21:39.709
outside cargo bay 12.

21:39.750 --> 21:41.083
Source?

21:41.125 --> 21:42.333
Unknown, sir.

21:42.375 --> 21:44.834
Computer, identify

21:42.375 --> 21:44.834
type of radiation.

21:44.875 --> 21:49.166
Emission is not consistent

21:44.875 --> 21:49.166
with any known radiation.

21:49.208 --> 21:51.291
It is subsiding, sir.

21:53.125 --> 21:56.000
WESLEY:

21:53.125 --> 21:56.000
What kind of radiation

21:53.125 --> 21:56.000
could do this?

21:58.000 --> 21:59.750
Make any sense to you?

21:59.792 --> 22:01.625
I don't recognize it.

22:01.667 --> 22:04.750
Not even the main deflector

22:01.667 --> 22:04.750
puts out that kind of spillage.

22:04.792 --> 22:06.250
Where would it

22:04.792 --> 22:06.250
be coming from?

22:06.291 --> 22:08.458
I don't know, Wes,

22:06.291 --> 22:08.458
but whatever it is

22:08.500 --> 22:11.583
it's capable of putting

22:08.500 --> 22:11.583
a hole in solid duranium.

22:28.917 --> 22:30.750
In a sense,

22:30.792 --> 22:32.917
we have already

22:30.792 --> 22:32.917
met Mrs. Apgar,

22:32.959 --> 22:35.500
so we shall dispense

22:32.959 --> 22:35.500
with introductions.

22:35.542 --> 22:37.375
PICARD:

22:35.542 --> 22:37.375
Mrs. Apgar,

22:37.417 --> 22:39.500
you understand the

22:37.417 --> 22:39.500
purpose of this hearing?

22:39.542 --> 22:42.041
TROI:

22:39.542 --> 22:42.041
We understand

22:42.083 --> 22:43.834
how difficult

22:42.083 --> 22:43.834
this will be for you.

22:43.875 --> 22:46.333
If you need a recess,

22:46.375 --> 22:47.750
please don't

22:46.375 --> 22:47.750
hesitate to ask.

22:47.792 --> 22:49.083
PICARD:

22:47.792 --> 22:49.083
Would you like

22:49.125 --> 22:51.208
to make a statement

22:49.125 --> 22:51.208
before we begin?

22:51.250 --> 22:52.917
No.

22:52.959 --> 22:55.417
I just know he did it.

22:55.458 --> 22:58.417
He killed my husband.

22:59.625 --> 23:01.125
Computer,

23:01.166 --> 23:04.083
load Manua

23:01.166 --> 23:04.083
Simulation One.

23:06.166 --> 23:07.792
Run program.

23:07.834 --> 23:09.875
If you greet them

23:07.834 --> 23:09.875
with such a long face

23:09.917 --> 23:11.208
they're going to assume

23:11.250 --> 23:13.583
something<i> is</i> wrong

23:11.250 --> 23:13.583
with the experiment.

23:13.625 --> 23:15.667
I just need time,

23:13.625 --> 23:15.667
a little more time.

23:15.709 --> 23:17.750
I'm certain they'll give you

23:15.709 --> 23:17.750
all the time you need

23:17.792 --> 23:20.792
if you just show

23:17.792 --> 23:20.792
a little charm.

23:20.834 --> 23:22.667
You do that so much better

23:22.709 --> 23:25.000
than I do.

23:27.041 --> 23:31.542
Manua, someday I'll be able

23:27.041 --> 23:31.542
to reward you

23:31.583 --> 23:33.208
for all

23:31.583 --> 23:33.208
your patience.

23:33.250 --> 23:35.333
I'll get you everything

23:33.250 --> 23:35.333
you ever dreamed of.

23:35.375 --> 23:37.709
I have all the reward I need.

23:37.750 --> 23:39.291
Now go on.

23:39.333 --> 23:41.875
I'll be right in.

23:43.834 --> 23:45.667
(<i> door opens and closes</i> )

23:45.709 --> 23:47.000
RIKER:

23:45.709 --> 23:47.000
Dr. Apgar?

23:47.041 --> 23:49.917
I'm Commander

23:47.041 --> 23:49.917
William Riker.

23:49.959 --> 23:51.542
Lieutenant Commander

23:49.959 --> 23:51.542
Geordi La Forge.

23:51.583 --> 23:53.458
My assistant, Tayna.

23:53.500 --> 23:56.291
Well, let's get on

23:53.500 --> 23:56.291
with it, shall we?

23:56.333 --> 23:57.917
Don't be in such a hurry, dear.

23:57.959 --> 24:00.333
Perhaps our guests would

23:57.959 --> 24:00.333
like some refreshment?

24:00.375 --> 24:02.583
My wife, Manua.

24:02.625 --> 24:04.709
A pleasure

24:02.625 --> 24:04.709
to meet you, Manua.

24:04.750 --> 24:06.000
NEL:

24:04.750 --> 24:06.000
I'm anxious

24:04.750 --> 24:06.000
to get started.

24:06.041 --> 24:07.542
If you wish.

24:07.583 --> 24:09.417
I must say, I resent your

24:07.583 --> 24:09.417
early arrival, Commander.

24:09.458 --> 24:10.709
I have much work to do.

24:10.750 --> 24:12.542
Doctor, I'll

24:10.750 --> 24:12.542
do everything

24:10.750 --> 24:12.542
in my power

24:12.583 --> 24:15.291
to make this as painless

24:12.583 --> 24:15.291
as possible for both of us.

24:15.333 --> 24:17.458
Do you assist

24:15.333 --> 24:17.458
your husband

24:15.333 --> 24:17.458
in his work?

24:17.500 --> 24:19.583
Oh, dear, no,

24:17.500 --> 24:19.583
I'm no scientist.

24:19.625 --> 24:21.583
No, neither am I.

24:21.625 --> 24:24.667
But I find this all fascinating,

24:21.625 --> 24:24.667
don't you?

24:24.709 --> 24:27.333
Mr. La Forge, why

24:24.709 --> 24:27.333
don't you take a look

24:27.375 --> 24:29.709
at the Doctor's

24:27.375 --> 24:29.709
experimental data.

24:29.750 --> 24:32.083
Later you can

24:29.750 --> 24:32.083
give me an overview.

24:32.125 --> 24:33.458
Fine, whatever.

24:33.500 --> 24:35.375
Starfleet will get its

24:33.500 --> 24:35.375
Krieger-wave converter.

24:35.417 --> 24:36.583
These things take time.

24:36.625 --> 24:38.333
I've had a few setbacks,

24:36.625 --> 24:38.333
